<td align="left"></td>
<td>Electricity</td>
<td>1000</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left"></td>
<td>Other</td>
<td>400</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left"></td>
<td>Bank</td>
<td>200</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left"></td>
<td>Trade Debtors Control A/c</td>
<td>3200</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left"></td>
<td>Trade Creditors Control A/c</td>
<td></td>
<td>700</td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left"></td>
<td></td>
<td>-------</td>
<td>-------</td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left"></td>
<td></td>
<td>6400</td>
<td>6400</td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left"></td>
<td></td>
<td>=====</td>
<td>=====</td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<th colspan="8">Both sides must have the same overall total</th>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<th colspan="8">Debits = Credits.</th>
</tr>
</table>
<p>The individual customer accounts are not to be listed in the trial balance, as the Trade debtors control a/c is the summary of each individual customer a/c.</p>
<p>The individual supplier accounts are not to be listed in the trial balance, as the Trade creditors control a/c is the summary of each individual supplier a/c.</p>
<p><b>Important note</b>: this example is designed to show double entry. There are methods of creating a trial balance that significantly reduce the time it takes to record entries in the general ledger and trial balance.</p>
<p><a name="Profit-and-loss_statement_and_balance_sheet" id="Profit-and-loss_statement_and_balance_sheet"></a></p>
