<p><a name="Example_2" id="Example_2"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Double-entry_bookkeeping_system&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Example 2">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Example 2</span></h2>
<p><a name="Transactions" id="Transactions"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Double-entry_bookkeeping_system&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Transactions">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Transactions</span></h4>
<p>XYZ Company is closing its books for the end of the month. Each of the daily journals has been summarized and the amounts are ready to be transferred to the general ledger. The amounts to be transferred are:</p>
<ul>
<li>Purchase raw materials on trade credit: $500,000</li>
<li>Pay workers from cash in bank to make goods: $1,500,000</li>
<li>Pay sales force from cash in bank to sell goods: $1,000,000</li>
<li>Sell goods for cash: $3,500,000</li>
</ul>
<p>To close the books for the month, we will adjust expenses and revenue to zero by appropriately crediting and debiting the income summary and then closing the income summary to <a href="/wiki/Retained_earnings" title="Retained earnings">retained earnings</a> (part of equity).</p>
<p>These items are entered in the ledger below; each matching credit and debit have been numbered to make finding them in the ledger easier.</p>
<p><a name="Ledgers" id="Ledgers"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Double-entry_bookkeeping_system&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: Ledgers">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Ledgers</span></h4>
<table class="wikitable">
<caption><b>General Ledger (in 000s)</b></caption>
<tr style="background:#efefef;">
<th>Transaction</th>
<th>Debit</th>
<th>Credit</th>
<th>Balance</th>
</tr>
<tr style="background:#efefef;">
<th colspan="4">Expenses</th>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left">Balance forward</td>
<td>&#160;</td>
<td>&#160;</td>
<td>-</td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left">1 Raw materials</td>
<td>$ 500</td>
<td>&#160;</td>
<td>$ 500</td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left">2 Labor</td>
<td>$ 1500</td>
<td>&#160;</td>
<td>$ 2000</td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left">3 Sales costs</td>
<td>$ 1000</td>
<td>&#160;</td>
<td>$ 3000</td>
</tr>
<tr align="right">
<td align="left">5 Income summary</td>
<td>&#160;</td>
<td>$ 3000</td>
<td>-</td>
</tr>
