<td>-</td>
<td>$ 500</td>
</tr>
<tr style="background:#efefef;" align="right">
<th>Total all accounts:</th>
<th>$13500</th>
<th>$13500</th>
<th>&#160;</th>
</tr>
</table>
<p>The amount in equity (in the form of retained earnings) has changed with a net credit of $500,000. Since equity has a normal balance of credit, this means there is now $500,000 <i>more</i> in equity than at the beginning of the month.</p>
